responded: Now I understand the issue. The problem is in the `php_libxml_unregister_node` function. When a node is freed during xinclude processing, the `nodeptr->node` is set to NULL (line 176), but the `php_libxml_node_ptr` structure itself is not freed. Later, when `dom_objects_free_storage` is called, it checks `((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node != NULL` but this check passes because the `php_libxml_node_ptr` structure still exists, even though the `node` field has been set to NULL.

The issue is that in `dom_objects_free_storage`, the code checks if `((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node != NULL` but then immediately accesses the node's type field without checking if the node is still valid.

Let me create a patch to fix this:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/php_dom.c b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
index 83dc12c6428..cbb126feabf 100644
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -1347,8 +1347,11 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)

 	zend_object_std_dtor(&intern->std);

-	if (intern->ptr != NULL && ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node != NULL) {
-		if (((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
+	if (intern->ptr != NULL) {
+		php_libxml_node_ptr *node_ptr = (php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr;
+		if (node_ptr->node != NULL) {
+			xmlNodePtr nodep = node_ptr->node;
+			if (nodep->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && nodep->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
 			php_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
 		} else {
 			php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
@@ -1356,6 +1359,7 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)
 		}
 		intern->ptr = NULL;
